# Design Tokens Format

## Core Structure
- Design tokens are name/value pairs in JSON format (.tokens.json)
- Each token has: `$type`, `$value`, optional `$description`
- Hierarchy: tokens grouped in nested objects for organization

## Token Types
- Color: `"$value": "#RRGGBB"` or RGB/HSL formats
- Dimension: `"$value": "8px"` (values with units)
- Also: font-family, font-weight, duration, number, etc.

## References
- Use syntax: `"$value": "{group.token-name}"`
- Creates relationships between tokens

## Example
```json
{
  "color": {
    "primary": {
      "$type": "color",
      "$value": "#0060df"
    },
    "text": { "$type": "color", "$value": "{color.primary}" }
  },
  "spacing": {
    "small": { "$type": "dimension", "$value": "8px" }
  }
}
```

## Best Practices
- Use consistent naming conventions
- Build relationships with references
- Group tokens logically